{"lemma":"سُورَةٌ","slug":"سُورَةٌ","root":"س.#.ر","root_slug":"س-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سُورَة","root":"سور","pos":"N","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21210"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sura, surah","examples":[{"text":"Holonym: اَلْقُرْآن (al-qurʔān)"},{"text":"Meronym: آيَة (ʔāya)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"severity, vehemence, sharpness"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Assigned to the root س و ر (s w r). It is not clear from which word it was borrowed, it might be from Classical Syriac ܫܘܽܪܳܐ (šūrā, “wall; also figuratively for any divider”), compare سُور (sūr, “wall”) from the same word, or from Classical Syriac ܣܽܘܪܓܳܕܳܐ (sūrgāḏā, “line; writing”), or from Hebrew סִדְרָה (siḏrā, “technical term for the section marks in the Hebrew scriptures”), or from Hebrew שִׁיר (šīr, “lyric song; poem”), or from a variant vocalization of Classical Syriac ܣܻܝܪܳܐ (sīrā, “thread; chapter, topical division of a book”)."},"ipa":["/suː.ra/","/saw.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21210","headword_ar":"سُورَةٌ","root":"swr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exalted, rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Es-Seed:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwarN","text_ar":"سُوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrN","text_ar":"سُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": [the latter of which is an anomalous pl.; or a coll. gen. n. of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrapN","text_ar":"سُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. of un., as in another sense mentioned below:] (M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrapN","text_ar":"سُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saworapN","text_ar":"سَوْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of glory, honour, dignity, or nobility; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"height"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (M, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu suwrapN fiY Almajodi","text_ar":"لَهُ سُورَةٌ فِى المَجْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has eminence in glory."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu suwrapN Ealayoka","text_ar":"لَهُ سُورَةٌ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has superiority, and rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station, over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above, thee; he is of higher rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity than thou."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwaru AlA_ibili","text_ar":"سُوَرُ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) [in the A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwarN mina AlA_ibili","text_ar":"سُوَرٌ مِنَ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suworu","text_ar":"سُوْرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibili","text_ar":"الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The excellent ones of camels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrapN","text_ar":"سُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, accord. to some, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardy and strong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrapN","text_ar":"سُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is goodly and tall, of structures."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") of anything. (IAar, TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrN","text_ar":"سُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A row of stones or bricks of a wall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K: in the L,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqN mino A^aEoraAqi AlHaAy^iTi","text_ar":"عَرَقٌ مِنْ اَعْرَاقِ الحَايِطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqN mn Euruwqi","text_ar":"عَرَقٌ من عُرُوقِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHAy^T","text_ar":"الحايط"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, as in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN Alx","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ الخ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any degree"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manozilap","text_ar":"مَنْزِلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a structure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrN","text_ar":"سُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [or this is a coll. gen. n.,] like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busorN","text_ar":"بُسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busorapN","text_ar":"بُسْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwarN","text_ar":"سُوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b6-  Hence its application in relation to the Kur-án, [to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chapter"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof,] because each of what are thus called forms one degree, or step, (S, M, * K,) distinct from another, (S, K,) or [leading] to another: (M:) or from the same word signifying “ eminence: ” (IAar:) or as being likened to the wall of a city: (B:) some pronounce it with hemz; (see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sA^r","text_ar":"سار"},{"kind":"text","text":";) but it is more common without: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwarN","text_ar":"سُوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwraAtN","text_ar":"سُورَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwaraAtN","text_ar":"سُوَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are also allowable. (S.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"token."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumaA suwrapN","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمَا سُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between them two is a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"token."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","M","IAar","B","TA","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}